---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import HelpCallout from "../../components/HelpCallout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Risk & protective factors"
  description="What raises the risk of gambling harm, and what helps protect against it — at the personal, family, and community level."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-header__eyebrow">
        <a href="/understand-gambling">← Understand gambling</a>
      </p>
      <h1>Risk &amp; protective factors</h1>
      <p class="page-header__lead">
        No single thing causes gambling harm. It grows out of a mix of factors —
        and many of them can be reduced or balanced out.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>What can raise risk</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Easy, frequent access — especially gambling on a phone, any time</li>
        <li>Starting to gamble at a young age</li>
        <li>An early big win that sets an expectation</li>
        <li>Acting on impulse, or chasing excitement</li>
        <li>Stress, anxiety, depression, or substance use</li>
        <li>Financial pressure</li>
        <li>A family history of gambling or other addictions</li>
        <li>Feeling isolated or without support</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Some activities and groups show higher risk in the research — for example,
        regular online gambling and sports betting, and men under 35.
      </p>

      <h2>What helps protect against harm</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Understanding how gambling works and the real odds</li>
        <li>Setting clear limits on time and money — and sticking to them</li>
        <li>Strong relationships and people to talk to</li>
        <li>Healthy ways to cope with stress and boredom</li>
        <li>Financial stability and money skills</li>
        <li>Knowing where to get help, and that it is free</li>
        <li>A full life — hobbies and activities beyond gambling</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Prevention is everyone's work</h2>
      <p>
        Reducing risk and building protection happens at every level: individuals
        making informed choices, families talking openly, and communities creating
        safer environments and easy access to help. That is the foundation of
        prevention practice.
      </p>

      <HelpCallout />

      <div class="sources">
        <h2>Learn more</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://www.ncpgambling.org/">National Council on Problem Gambling</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.samhsa.gov/">SAMHSA — behavioral health prevention</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
